data.text: Yesterday I got the impression we were all ready to go, so long as I didn't mind working off of the sheet you sent, which I didn't. So for now I just wait until a card is moved to column you mentioned?
Yoni, I have been working on this for almost 2 hours already! I have just completed Berakhot 7. Was I told yesterday not to start?
@shoshanakahan Please don't do any work on the mishna unless it's in the align column. Any work done on cards in the To Parse column will be erased.
never mind. The Mishna has ה' and that's what I'm putting
What's our way of writing Shem HaShem? ה' or יי. I think we had the first and now I'm finding the second. Other version has ה'
Sefaria's Mishna spells out "Rav" or "Rabi," whereas traditionally it's ר'. Should I assume we always have that right and leave it? i.e: רבי טורפון rather than revert to ר' in case we made a mistake?

Sefaria recognizes everything in Sefaria as a reference. In the case of the mishnah the only thing quoted will be Tanach so it should be fairly straightforward.

There's no standard for whether the citation comes before or after the quote - however the text does it is fine.
no

Should the citation always follow the quote? What's the Sefaria standard?
